[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 3:15-16",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Deuteronomy 3:15-16",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Gilead — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "That is, the half part of Gilead. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "To Machir —",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "That is, unto the children of Machir, son of Manasseh, for Machir was now dead. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Half the valley — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Or rather, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "to the middle of the river: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "for the word rendered ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "half, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "signifies commonly ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "middle, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and the same Hebrew word means both a ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "valley ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and a ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "brook, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "or ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "river. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And this sense is agreeable to the truth, that their land extended from Gilead unto Arnon, and, to speak exactly, to the middle of that river; for as that river was the border between them and others, so one half of it belonged to them, as the other half did to others; see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 12:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", where the same thing is expressed in the same words, in the Hebrew, though our translators render them there, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "from the middle of the river, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and here, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "half of the valley.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "3:12-20 This country was settled on the Reubenites, Gadites, and half the tribe of Manasseh: see Nu 32. Moses repeats the condition of the grant to which they agreed. When at rest, we should desire to see our brethren at rest too, and should be ready to do what we can towards it; for we are not born for ourselves, but are members one of another.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "These Geshurites held territory adjoining, if not included within, Bashan. They are not to be confounded with those mentioned in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 13:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", who were neighbors of the Philistines ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Samuel 17:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The exact position of Maachah like that of Geshur cannot be ascertained; but it was no doubt among the fastnesses which lay between Bashan and the kingdom of Damascus, and on the skirts of Mount Hermon.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Unto this day - This expression, like our \"until now,\" does not, as used in the Bible, necessarily imply that the time spoken of as elapsed is long. It may here denote the duration to the time then present of that which had been already some months accomplished. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Unto this day - This expression, like our \"until now,\" does not, as used in the Bible, necessarily imply that the time spoken of as elapsed is long. It may here denote the duration to the time then present of that which had been already some months accomplished. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
